Privacy Policy
General
This Privacy Policy explains how TV Master - Smart TV Remote Control ("TV Master", "our", "us" or "we") collect, use, and share your personal data. Here, we care about your personal data, so we have prepared this Privacy Policy to explain how we collect, use, and share it.
Our Privacy Policy details the personal data received about you, how we process it, and your rights and obligations in relation to your personal data. By using or accessing the Service, and others agree to the terms of this Service ("Users").
What kinds of information are collected?
- Information Provided by You or Collected with Your permission. Information Related to Your Use of the Services.
- Interactive Features.
- Surveys.
- Information about the device itself:  IP address, device name, device type, device model, operation system, device GPS location.
- Information that can be used to access the App: Names, email address, phone number, country.
- Information about the internet connection: Network provider, network type, browser type.
- Others: Advertising ID, IMEI, OAID, IDFV, IDFA, GAID, zip code.
We may invite you to participate in surveys. If you decide to fill out the forms, you may be asked to provide certain information which may include personal information.
How Do we use the information?
We may use the information we collect for a variety of business purposes, including:
To provide the Services or Information Requested.
Fulfill our contract with you;
To tailor and deliver personalized content to you;
Manage your information;
Respond to questions, comments, and other requests;
Provide access to certain areas, functionalities, and features of our Services; and Answer requests for customer or technical support.
Administrative Purposes.
Pursue legitimate business interests, such as research and development (including marketing research), network and information security, and fraud prevention;
Carry out analytics;
Measure interest and engagement in the services;
Develop of new products and services;
Improve our products and Services;
Ensure internal quality control and safety;
Verify individual identity;
Carry out audits;
Communicate with you about activities on the Services and changes to our agreements;
Prevent and prosecute potentially prohibited or illegal activities;
Enforce our agreements; and Comply with our legal obligations.
What information do we share with Third Parties?
We may share the information that we have collected from you as described below:
Information Shared with Our Advertising Partners.
We may engage third-party advertising partners to collect information and serve advertising on and through the Services. When you use our Services, these third-party advertising partners may collect information regarding your activities and your device (e.g., mobile device identifiers, page(s) visited, location, time of day). These advertising partners may use this information (and similar information collected from other services) for the purposes of delivering personalized advertisements to you when you visit our Services and third-party services within their networks. This practice is commonly referred to as "interest-based advertising" or "personalized advertising."
Information Shared with Our Services Providers.
We may engage third-party service providers to work with us to administer and provide the Services. The types of service providers to whom we entrust personal information include service providers for (i) the provision of the Services; (ii) the provision of information, products, and other services you have requested; (iii) analytics; (iv) marketing and advertising; (v) customer service activities; and (vi) the provision IT and related services.
Software Development Kits.
We may use third-party software development kits ("SDKs") as part of the functionality of our App. SDKs typically collect your mobile device identifier and information related to your use of the Services. SDKs may allow third parties including analytics and advertising partners to collect your information for various purposes including providing analytics services and personalized advertising.
Information about Our third-party SDKs.
